<subSubSection id="4128650382E44062C04A645C4C8992E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type species">
<paragraph id="C272DD407A34243673BF3E592CD7A621" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type species by original designation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B293569FFF72BB5984E5FBB547E35BAC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="D2B70F57CFBCD12759BEB92341450000" authorityName="Davis &amp; Kuo" authorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia daliensis" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis id="135421BF1E0F1A2322A74E607500832F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Kuo in 
<bibRefCitation id="2B02109ADCD203B8699BBD197321E125" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al., 1985</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8CC1CC8C46E0385297E1DB93CDD1C726" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="synonym">
<paragraph id="B83DE8D08BD6C83631345353312DBB16" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Synonym.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A07F0226308C9AFBB51071FDB22C3BC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="766A4FA0C380E75BCB629BBF257EF2C4" authority="Melville, 1956" authorityName="Melville" authorityYear="1956" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudobythinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudobythinella" order="Mesogastropoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="398A897A6BDFC00EC2A4C69503FCE574" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudobythinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979. Not Melville, 1956. Type species by original designation: 
<taxonomicName id="51240F3B29562D1EBA7D6C4986463D23" authority="Y.-Y.Liu &amp; W.-Z.Zhang, 1979" authorityName="Y. -Y. Liu &amp; W. -Z. Zhang" authorityYear="1979" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Pseudobythinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudobythinella jianouensis" order="Mesogastropoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jianouensis">
<emphasis id="D31D2FBEA5163E1921E3F21B566B570A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pseudobythinella jianouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB60A7435108DD965E70167B3B9E3452" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="B72D89E4677DE4A6F71CD6A89F48111F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22587329988C9229CA522FBDAA06178B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shell ovoid to elongate ovoid or conical, smooth or with spiral microsculpture on the proto- and/or teleoconch. Apex conspicuously and more or less obliquely flattened. Aperture varying from ovoid-elliptical to circular; its palatal side curved and gradually passing into the basal side. Peristome continuous, attached at the parietal side or more or less protruding. Umbilicus minute or closed. Parietal part of the aperture smooth or with a lamella; columella smooth or with 2 spiral lamellae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADA147701C01E23D125A0D9169E88072" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AAD5CE416D595550D1CE040D8BBFFC85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE5AB9F4FF4069816309730E33886F3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Molecular data, which are available for only a limited number of the amnicolid species, are inconclusive regarding the status of 
<taxonomicName id="E09886412845837DDDB53A9913DE4222" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C972D6F8D63AB1EDD4F17757B2ABBCBB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus 
<taxonomicName id="27B8396FAE6A33C58B708391ACC95FDF" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Akiyoshia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="61EA18AA4BB50A0069AC4EAE5866B824" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Akiyoshia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1954 
<taxonomicName id="1AB4682FA573CD90246E2D0D6B96DA98" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" genus="Akiyoshia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="class">Gastropoda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="548AC1258ABC40D284BDB61D8D2766F1" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1954" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Truncatelloidea">Truncatelloidea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B4399CACA169B5C7E52E73E8004DB1B4" authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1863" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Amnicolidae</taxonomicName>
) (see also the more comprehensive phylogenetic reconstruction in 
<bibRefCitation id="C7A9979EB3C40BC5E5873F148677877E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">Gittenberger et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). No DNA data are known for the type species of these nominal taxa, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="4A0A96D2659F60CCECE0CB1E15B910AD" genus="E." lsidName="E. daliensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="daliensis">
<emphasis id="3435022548E694ED306B8D105A07140F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. daliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Kuo, 1985 and 
<taxonomicName id="8C626BDC5FD42C0C9D59AA2AAA2DDF31" genus="A." lsidName="A. uenoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="uenoi">
<emphasis id="88CA9A0DB06363730EF762D2C5BBA074" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. uenoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1954. Furthermore, the species that are generally called 
<taxonomicName id="3FDA24B291867463BCFDFA3716042778" baseAuthorityName="Y. -Y. Liu &amp; W. -Z. Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1979" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia jianouensis" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="jianouensis">
<emphasis id="64F72592B8FA9402F9FD50D53B387DC2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia jianouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Liu &amp; Zhang, 1979) and 
<taxonomicName id="D25F94EB1B2C2D2D28D213CEC8FEC4FB" authorityName="Kuroda &amp; Habe" authorityYear="1958" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Akiyoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Akiyoshia kobayashii" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="kobayashii">
<emphasis id="5CBF6D2EA8879978B2AC095DEDF7C0A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Akiyoshia kobayashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kuroda &amp; Habe, 1958 are sister species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8DD28CE1913FB551A987C453E2483D6F" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 7. Maximum likelihood tree reconstructed with RAxML BlackBox (Stamatakis et al. 2008; GTR + G substitution model for each partition and 100 bootstrap replicates) based on the COI and 16 S rRNA dataset of Liu et al. (2014) and Guan et al. (2008), with new data in red. Numbers on branches denote bootstrap values&gt; 50." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641075" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">7</figureCitation>
) that should be congeneric by definition. At present, their ranges in China and Japan, respectively, have been decisive for the generic classification. Pending additional data that can help solve this problem convincingly, we opted to still use the current, contradictory nomenclature (see also notes under 
<taxonomicName id="377A51CBB035D8FBB410E84011BC9C81" genus="E." lsidName="E. norbui" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="norbui">
<emphasis id="511E7ED9907F0C69F792D97F60A6F830" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. norbui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F7B849795B7CBCC8DBC6F8C97B05F43" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="59FA242082507A416EDD6D6576D1E820" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B9EB4DCA35932ED1962892E267950DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="CF02660E45D0FEE122A610938E5ED3D1" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4369DC137B97362D87834DBFCE9CD86" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially reported from a wide range in southern China, where it has been recorded with various species from the provinces of Yunnan, Sichuan, Guangxi, Hubei, Hunan, and Fujian (
<bibRefCitation id="51C55CC1416BC9D6C76375527E601CB1" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="48 - 78" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" refId="B5" refString="Davis, GM, Kuo, Y-H, Hoagland, KE, Chen, P-L, Yang, H-M, Chen, D-J, 1985. Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 137: 48 - 78, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" title="Erhaia, a new genus and new species of Pomatiopsidae from China (Gastropoda: Rissoacea)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4064860" volume="137" year="1985">Davis et al. 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E294998B5BA5C961FDADDF327347FF9C" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="391 - 427" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" refId="B3" refString="Davis, GM, Kang, ZB, 1995. Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 146: 391 - 427, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" title="Advances in the Systematics of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) from the People's Republic of China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065020" volume="146" year="1995">Davis and Kang 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F8560C01E1CAFE1E36927F34EBE3ADA1" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B4" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FB7410979EC5A9D1454DC55978CA5606" DOI="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="453 - 459" refId="B24" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Gong, X, Liu, H-X, 2000. Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia. The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene 62: 453 - 459, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" title="Erhaia (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): phylogenetic relationships and the question of Paragonimus coevolution in Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.4269/ajtmh.2000.62.453" volume="62" year="2000">Wilke et al. 2000</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="D187C3D8685A7DB2B028F557B69544F4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" author="Wilke, T" journalOrPublisher="The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Wilke, T, Davis, GM, Falniowski, A, Giusti, F, Bodon, M, Szarowska, M, 2001. Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1-21. https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" title="Molecular systematics of Hydrobiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Rissooidea): testing monophyly and phylogenetic relationships. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 151: 1 - 21." url="https://doi.org/10.1635/0097-3157(2001)151[0001:MSOHMG]2.0.CO;2" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E6BD67389013260727F18F4F42978912" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" author="Liu, L" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B16" refString="Liu, L, Huo, G-N, He, H-B, Zhou, B, Attwood, SW, 2014. A phylogeny for the pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: e29. https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" title="A phylogeny for the pomatiopsidae (Gastropoda: Rissooidea): a resource for taxonomic, parasitological and biodiversity studies. BMC Evolutionary Biology 14: e 29." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/1471-2148-14-29" year="2014">Liu et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Regarding its occurrence in Japan, see foregoing notes. One species was described from northern India (
<bibRefCitation id="F527E01748ED670279BA94C258C0EA5E" author="Davis, GM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="273 - 299" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" refId="B4" refString="Davis, GM, Rao, S, 1997. Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China. Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 148: 273 - 299, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" title="Discovery of Erhaia (Gastropoda: Pomatiopsidae) in northern India with description of a new genus of Erhaiini from China." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4065055" volume="148" year="1997">Davis and Rao 1997</bibRefCitation>
), three additional species were described from Nepal (
<bibRefCitation id="B8D9B9FAB7214418E70F5980A205E2F2" author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B21" refString="Nesemann, H, Sharma, S, Sharma, G, Khanal, SN, Pradhan, B, Shah, DN, Tachamo, RD, 2007. Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga river system (Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea, 57-102." title="Class Gastropoda. In: Nesemann H, Sharma S, Sharma G, Khanal SN, Pradhan B, Shah DN, Tachamo RD (Eds) Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga river system (Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea, 57 - 102." year="2007">Nesemann et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and, most recently, three species were described from Bhutan (
<bibRefCitation id="EC236C4C057BF41C80E21B7684F7E7B7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="21 - 28" refId="B7" refString="Gittenberger, E, Sherub, S, Stelbrink, B, 2017. Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan. ZooKeys 679: 21 - 28, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" title="Erhaia Davis &amp; Kuo (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae) also in Bhutan." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.679.13326" volume="679" year="2017">Gittenberger et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5B3BA3220A0595B999CC4F8A1C645444" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
). Here, we describe a fourth species from Bhutan and present, for the first time, a map of all known records of the genus (see Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9B22F1E6BA08B12AA4696CE7D22CBA52" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of Erhaia species across Asia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641071" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
and Table 
<tableCitation id="F3A4A5D2EBAD9546DAEC03637EA32A96" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Distribution of Erhaia species with coordinates (sorted from west to east) either provided by the source publication or estimated based on the locality information therein." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F5AE33FB49EC640676A0FD6F3C1BA1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="0F5AE33FB49EC640676A0FD6F3C1BA1D">1</tableCitation>
). As usual, it is unknown where snails may have been looked for in vain and thus our distribution maps (Figs 
<figureCitation id="58B0659DA9AB873CDD3714F5D72A49E9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution of Erhaia species across Asia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641071" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E370EAE2ABDE8D9A0B05FD5AE8DBAAFC" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution of Erhaia species described for Bhutan. Note that E. jannei and E. pelkiae were found to occur syntopically." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641074" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
) may represent human sampling activity rather than the real range of 
<taxonomicName id="67D8246F39CE69BDBFEDAA2112C0BDB7" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17E368FB5DB75870C005AE505671F21E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Contrary to 
<bibRefCitation id="244CAD17FA6709643A7B0BBFC9F217F5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" author="Gittenberger, E" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 17" refId="B8" refString="Gittenberger, E, Leda, P, Wangchuck, J, Gyeltshen, C, Stelbrink, B, 2020. The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya. ZooKeys 929: 1 - 17, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" title="The genera Erhaia and Tricula (Gastropoda, Rissooidea, Amnicolidae and Pomatiopsidae) in Bhutan and elsewhere in the eastern Himalaya." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.929.49987" volume="929" year="2020">Gittenberger et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, in the absence of DNA data, we refer to 
<taxonomicName id="1FBF37F1F32FF744FB7AD278EB3390A1" genus="E." lsidName="E. chandeshwariensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chandeshwariensis">
<emphasis id="8DE7C3E619A21C05612B70586A50E177" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. chandeshwariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nesemann &amp; S. Sharma, 2007 as a species closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="7E19D78FE0455A5FF4AA8CB3A629B421" genus="E." lsidName="E. nainatalensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nainatalensis">
<emphasis id="127E64402CBFD28552B73DB1F7670EDD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. nainatalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Davis &amp; Rao, 1997. The shells cannot be distinguished, but the type localities are over 600 km apart, which makes conspecificity unlikely in 
<taxonomicName id="49529FDDCBCAC8A960979F8B74CE1384" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CC0E7BB1496531931DDB40F03895857" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Remarkable facts are the allopatric distribution and diversification in this genus in general, the syntopic occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="F578CE293B83F38A7B3840D0C12CF92D" genus="E." lsidName="E. jannei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="jannei">
<emphasis id="460E5BB73B068B25EF6E5A531CF22862" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. jannei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gittenberger &amp; Stelbrink, 2020 and 
<taxonomicName id="781DEC84EFF31B5F88DC7AA878C1F4A0" genus="E." lsidName="E. pelkiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pelkiae">
<emphasis id="3243EF3293441C5FC1E004740D4457A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. pelkiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gittenberger &amp; Gyeltshen, 2020 in Bhutan (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ED671C4F694511C18CD8D3D02248D241" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 6. Distribution of Erhaia species described for Bhutan. Note that E. jannei and E. pelkiae were found to occur syntopically." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641074" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6</figureCitation>
), and that of 
<taxonomicName id="D66E1D83804CD478189E911CBD81B8C2" genus="E." lsidName="E. banepaensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="banepaensis">
<emphasis id="F4C12CFB24AF6BF701689849CB1C65A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. banepaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nesemann &amp; S. Sharma, 2007 with either 
<taxonomicName id="9E698419896DF7B7A1DA40CF73555B91" genus="E." lsidName="E. chandeshwariensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="chandeshwariensis">
<emphasis id="63031BFB7A15FDA2381B840FCCD433A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. chandeshwariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="5822BB1471C00ADECEA667929E8FF73B" genus="E." lsidName="E. sugurensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sugurensis">
<emphasis id="9600C239106031BAFDE10CAA7AA5AC21" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. sugurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nesemann, Shah &amp; Tachamo, 2007 in Nepal (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E1494BBBA2E599BE6368B2C706D28193" captionStart="Figures 3–5" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 3 - 5. Erhaia norbui sp. nov. from the type locality, district Haa, Uesu, Naychu, ca. 2700 m a. s. l. 3 holotype, NBCB 1239 (H = 2.3 mm) and paratypes used for DNA analyses (4 UGSB 25956, H = 1.5 mm 5 UGSB 25957, H = 1.8 mm). Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figures3-5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641073" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="83EFD14B74310947E9E9AC9E133238C8" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1085.77900.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/641074" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 6" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="43188D5D7B61937822E2F00AFC8A4379" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="F184817CDDA718E54EF080C350B6B9F0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 6.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="6CD3294737475C9F62AC53B5A50A905A" class="Gastropoda" family="Amnicolidae" genus="Erhaia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Erhaia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1ED1FBE56C5D736EEC3293B87F88AF03" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erhaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species described for Bhutan. Note that 
<taxonomicName id="95DEEE7E541D39E1B2A7F1244E3DC0D1" genus="E." lsidName="E. jannei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="jannei">
<emphasis id="98AF362E6F0553D93C1A959CF4557761" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. jannei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="430025C0E45ECBA2FD26D5A910160271" genus="E." lsidName="E. pelkiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pelkiae">
<emphasis id="74FDA2CAC8D0ED099014814A684EB113" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. pelkiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found to occur syntopically.
</paragraph>
